dcterms:creator: R. A. Fisher
dcterms:description: Fisher’s Iris dataset is well-studied within the fields of machine learning and statistics and commonly employed as a benchmark for assessing classification algorithms. This dataset encompasses measurements of four distinct features taken from three species of iris flowers.
dcterms:title: Fisher’s Iris Dataset

dcterms:creator: A. C. Coster
J. H. Field
dcterms:description: The starch grain dataset encapsulates representative information for starch grains from seven distinct species. It includes 944 units (grains), each described by 16 morphological features, and is used for identifying plant micro-fossils of unknown species origin.
dcterms:title: Starch Grain Dataset
